Ecological notes : very common in broad-leaved and mixed woodland; conifer plantations; ancient pine woodland; stunted oak woodland on moorland; carr woodland; common on dry and damp heathland; common on wetlands including all types of fen, mires, bogs, ditches, sedge beds and water meadows; sea cliff; grazed meadow; calcareous grassland; open and high montane habitats. iii–x.
